The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, April 28, 2003  Calcutta Column
 
	Most English-medium schools direct guardians to buy textbooks  from shops of their choice. These shops do not offer any  discount, whereas the same books can cost much less if bought  from a College Street shop. The schools also order students  to get their uniforms from specific outlets. Why doesnt  the government look into these unhealthy sources of revenue? 
	 Piyal Mukherjee,
 Lake Town.  
	The computerised railway reservation counter near Chittaranjan  Avenue is not equipped to serve customers. An inquiry counter  needs to be set up. More reservation counters are needed.  
	Danish Khan,
 College Street. 

